message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Haiti in the past five years was the assassination of President Jovenel Moïse on July 7, 2021. This event shocked the nation and had significant political and social implications. The assassination led to a power vacuum and political instability in the country, exacerbating the ongoing economic and social challenges faced by Haiti. The event also drew international attention and raised concerns about the country's security and governance.
